<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef865e62-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2565"><num value="2565">§ 2565.</num><heading> Attorney fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The court in exceptional cases may award reasonable attorney fees to the prevailing party.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef865e63-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/577/tIII/s125">Pub. L. 91–577, title III, § 125</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1556">84 Stat. 1556</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
